  "texts": [
    "The DNN model has three components: (1) a front-end convolutional vision network that reflects processing in the optic lobe;",
    "(2) a bottleneck layer of LC units in which each model LC unit represents the summed activity of neurons of the same LC type (that is, the overall activity level of an optic glomerulus); and (3) a decision network with dense connections that maps LC responses to behaviour, reflecting downstream processing in the central brain and ventral nerve cord (Fig. 1a).",
    "We imposed the bottleneck layer to have the same number of units as LC neuron types we manipulated, and our goal was to identify a one-to-one mapping between model LC units and LC neuron types.",
    "We did not incorporate biological realism into the vision and decision",
